description:
The Armageddon is over and The Devil has won. In this latest collection of stories culled from the hit Shadowline Web comic series, learn how the previous NIGHTMARE WORLD tales of Irish fairy-folk, vengeful zombie killers, alien ultra-heroes, Cthulhu and more combine with these 13 new tales of terror to reveal Lucifer's sinister plan to control Creation, revealing the haunted underbelly of a monstrous world all too similar to our own in the chilling tradition of ?Tales from the Crypt? and ?The Twilight Zone.?

Includes an introduction by GARY (Deadworld) REED, re-mastered art, a bonus prose story and more!

Softcover, 128 pages, full color.

description: The Complete Wash Tubbs and Captain Easy by Roy Crane were published by the Flying Buttress Classics Library. Widely considered to be one of the first great adventure strips, Wash Tubbs the wise-cracking, girl-chasing opportunist and soldier of fortune Captain Easy are back for more fun and adventure. Volume 17 (1941-1942) reprints Crane's classic comic strips with an introduction by George Crawbuck. While Wash struggles with married life, Easy continues his adventures as a special agent for the FBI. Plus Lulu Belle tracks Wolf-Girl in the big city and Bull Dawson returns.

Meanwhile, Wolverine and Kid Omega travel to an intergalactic casino to win enough money to keep the Jean Grey School going! And when a billion Brood invade the school, Kitty, Broo the Broodling and an army of Bamfs must face a new, unstoppable foe!
